https://ssd-disclosure.com/ssd-advisory-overlayfs-pe/ (can get instant root Linux < 5.11)

Use gobusters dns feature for enumeration of subdomains

steghide for images, stegseek for passphrases

if uploading to ftp ensure that the proper file permissions are set

https://gitlab.com/kalilinux/packages/linux-exploit-suggester - Maybe there are some exploits that you can use already?

If a program is calling a function without using an explicit path, it could be intercepted and set to run a different program. https://www.shh.ninja/posts/security/htb-oopsie/#privilege-escalation
